<FIRST>r w AM-RouletteShooting     11-25 0154</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Roulette Shooting,150</SECOND>
<HEAD>10-Year-Old Dies Playing Russian Roulette</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 10-year-old boy playing Russian roulette
with his father's gun died Friday after putting the revolver to his
head and pulling the trigger as four friends urged him to put the
weapon away, authorities said.
   The boy, identified as John Thomas, loaded the .38-caliber
revolver while his mother was at the grocery store, officials said.
   The other youngsters at the Thomas home told authorities that
nothing happened the first time John pulled the trigger, but that
it went off the second time.
   The friends urged John to put the gun away, police said.
   ``All of them seemed to recognize the danger, except him,'' said
police Lt. Ronald Harvey. ``They said it was dangerous, it was
stupid and the gun could possibly go off.''
   John was pronounced dead at Children's Hospital National Medical
Center. He was the son of John and Mary Thomas.
</TEXT>
