<HEAD>New Meetings in Hanoi</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   U.S. and Vietnamese technical specialists will
meet in Hanoi next week to discuss cooperation in the effort to
account for Americans still missing from the Vietnam War.
   Lt. Col. Joe Harvey, commander of the Joint Casualty Resolution
Center in Hawaii, will lead the U.S. delegation to the meeting
Monday through Wednesday, the Pentagon said Friday.
