<FIRST>u i AM-Dubcek-Excerpts     11-25 0196</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Dubcek-Excerpts,0200</SECOND>
<HEAD>Excerpts of Dubcek Speech to Rally</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Czechoslovakia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PRAGUE, Czechoslovakia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The following are the highlights
of Alexander Dubcek's speech before a rally of 500,000 people in
Saturday. His comments were made in Slovak and translated by The
Associated Press:
   The political leadership has lost touch with the people and the
crisis has deepened. ... The changes did not meet the demands of
the people. ...
   They (government leaders) are telling us that the street is not
the place for things to be solved, but I say the street was and is
the place. The voice of the street must be heard. ...
   I appeal to the Central Committee of the party to take the
initiative and the ideas (of the reform groups) very seriously. ..
. We appeal to the Central Committee that those who have caused the
stagnation leave their posts and not obstruct further development
of this country. ...
   Our efforts (in 1968) were crushed, but the ideals of democracy,
freedom and humanity live on in us and in the new generation. ...
Democratic renewal can only succeed when the slogan `All power to
the people' is fully realized.
</TEXT>
