<FIRST>u i AM-Germany-Reunification     11-25 0149</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Germany-Reunification,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>Magazine: U.S. Official Says Eventual German Reunification Inevitable</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-East Germany</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAMBURG, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A West German news magazine
reported Saturday that Lawrence Eagleburger, U.S. deputy secretary
of state, said he thinks eventual German reunification is
inevitable.
   ``For me there is no question that Germany will be reunited.
This process is now inevitable,'' the Hamburg-based Der Spiegel
quoted him as saying.
   But Spiegel said he added: ``I can't simply tell you how long
that will take.''
   Spiegel quoted him as saying there might be some who are made
nervous by the prospect of eventual German reunification, but that
there is no need to be concerned ``about a democratic Germany
united in peace and freedom.''
   Spiegel printed Eagleburger's comments in German, and they were
translated back into English by The Associated Press.
   The magazine did not say where the U.S. official was interviewed
or when.
</TEXT>
