<FIRST>r a AM-SlashVictims     11-25 0184</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Slash Victims,0189</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Find Bodies of Woman, Teen-ager with Throats Slashed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EVERETT, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The bodies of a woman and a teen-ager
believed to be her daughter were found with their throats slashed
and their mouths gagged with duct tape in a basement apartment
Saturday, police said.
   Police entered the apartment around 10:50 a.m. after the
landlord reported an odor from the basement that he first noticed a
couple of days before, said Lt. Charles Savage.
   The victims were not identified pending notification of
relatives. Savage said the two lived in the apartment in this city
of 43,000 just outside Boston.
   The body of the older woman, who was about 35 years old, was
found in a bedroom, Savage said. The teen-ager, who was about 14,
was found in a closet.
   ``Their throats were slashed, they had stab wounds and there was
duct tape over their mouths,'' he said.
   The time and cause of death have not been determined, said a
technician with the Suffolk County Medical Examiner's office who
would not give his name.
   There were no suspects, Savage said.
</TEXT>
